events.description:
The magical adventure begins with Shahbaz, a prehistoric bird. Together with his friends, Rachel and Felix, they travel across beautiful landscapes and the mysteries of time, featuring artistic interpretations of the Industrial Revolution, the Silk Road era, Mayan Pyramids, Underwater World and African Savanna. As Shahbaz’s friends discover more about themselves, will they find the courage to be who they really are? events.title: [API] DinoVenture
events.description:
Explore lush primitive jungles and navigate through breathtaking landscapes where dinosaurs roam free. Feel the rush of adrenaline as you twist, turn, and dodge prehistoric predators through 6 different movements. 
Put on your VR goggles, hold on tight and make a daring escape! 
What to Expect



Ticket purchased has a validity period of 90 days upon date of purchase. 
DinoVenture operating hours: 10am - 10pm (Last boarding 9.40pm)
Guests must be between 110cm and 190cm tall.
Maximum weight limit is 100kg.
Children under 12 years old must be accompanied by an adult.
The VR experience is NOT suitable for the following: 



Pregnant women 
Guest who require mobility assistance 
Guest who are prone to motion sickness
Guest with fear of enclosed spaces
Guest who are sensitive to strobe effects or flashing lights
Guest who have recently undergone surgery
Guest under the influence of alcohol 
Guest with history of Epilepsy, Heart or blood pressure conditions, Back or neck conditions




Admission will be at the discretion of the attraction host, on a first come first serve basis. 
By entering into Dinoventure, guests are aware of the attraction's prevailing operating guidelines. You may refer to https://www.mountfaberleisure.com/dinoventure-safety-guidelines/ for the operating guidelines.

events.title: National Orchid Garden
events.description: Since 1859, orchids have been closely associated with the Gardens. The products of the Gardens' orchid breeding programme, which began in 1928, deserve a place where they can be displayed in their full splendour. The very design of these orchids is, one could say, 'hand-crafted' by the Gardens' horticultural staff, dedicated to bringing out the finest in any hybrid cross. With over 1000 species and 2000 hybrids on display, the splendour of these gorgeous blooms is absolutely a sight to behold at the National Orchid Garden.

events.title: Singapore Discovery Centre’s Singapore Navy Museum
events.description: First opened in 1987 in Sembawang Camp, the Singapore Navy Museum relocated to Changi Naval Base in May 2012. Following a decade in operation, the Museum underwent a complete overhaul and refresh of its exhibits in 2022. Designed to honour the past, celebrate the present and inspire the future, the Singapore Navy Museum is home to various artefacts from the RSN’s early ships such as RSS Panglima and RSS Singapura, as well as more contemporary artefacts such as equipment from our Challenger-class submarines, as well as other classes of ships.Reservation Procedure ·         Visit Singapore Navy Museum Booking site (Shop | Defence Collective Singapore (defencecollectivesg.com))·         Select either Singapore Navy Museum(Foreigners) or Singapore Navy Museum(Singapore Citizens and PR) and click “Book Now”·         Enter the number of tickets required, visit date and time, click “Add to cart”·         Complete your details·         Apply the promo code provided and proceed to check out. Please note that codes for the same attraction can be stacked per transaction.
